 0228:     '''A class for generating a spatial compartmental model with commute data
 0229: 
 0230:     Let :math:`\\mu, \\nu` denote spatial index and i, j denote age group index.
 0231: 
 0232:     .. math::
 0233:         C^{\\mu\\nu}_{ij} = \\frac{1}{N^\\mu_i} \widetilde{C}^{\\mu \\nu}_{ij}
 0234: 
 0235:     Parameters
 0236:     ----------
 0237:     b: float
 0238:         Parameter b in the above equation
 0239:     populations: np.array(n_loc, M)
 0240:         Populations of regions by age groups. Here n_loc is the number of regions
 0241:         and M is the number of age groups.
 0242:     areas: np.array(n_loc)
 0243:         Areas of the geographical regions.
 0244:     commutes: np.array(n_loc, n_loc, M)
 0245:         Each entry commute[mu, nu, i] needs to be the number of people of age
 0246:         group i commuting from :math:`\\mu` to :math:`\\nu`.
 0247:         Entries with :math:`\\mu = \\nu` are ignored.
 0248:     '''

 0369:     '''A class for generating a minimal spatial compartmental model
 0370: 
 0371:     Let :math:`\\mu, \\nu` denote spatial index and i, j denote age group index,
 0372: 
 0373:     .. math::
 0374:         C^{\\mu\\nu}_{ij} = \\frac{1}{a_{ij}} k^{\\mu\\nu} g^{\\mu\\nu}_{ij} f^{\\mu\\nu}_{ij} C_{ij}
 0375: 
 0376:     where
 0377:     .. math::
 0378:         a_{ij} = \sum_{\mu\nu} k^{\mu\nu}_{ij} g^{\mu\nu}_{ij} \sqrt{ \frac{ N_i^\mu N_j^\nu} {N_i N_j}}
 0379:         k^{\mu \nu} = \exp ( - b_{\mu\nu} | r^\mu - r^\nu |) \\
 0380:         b_{\mu, \nv} = (\rho^\mu \rho^\nu)^{-c} \\
 0381:         g^{\mu\nu}_{ij} = (\rho^\mu_i \rho^\nu_j)^b \\
 0382:         f^{\mu\nu}_{ij} = \sqrt{ \frac{N_i N_j^\nu}{N_i^\mu N_j}}
 0383: 
 0384:     where :math:`C_{ij}` is the non-spatial age structured contact matrix,
 0385:     :math:`\rho^\mu_i` is the population density of age group i
 0386:     in spatial location :math:`\mu`,
 0387:     :math:`\rho_i` is the total population density of age group i,
 0388:     :math:`r^\mu` is the spatial position of the :math:`\mu`th location,
 0389:     :math:`N_i^\mu` is the population of the age group i at :math:`\mu`,
 0390:     :math:`N_i` is the total population of the age group i,
 0391:     and b, c are free parameters
 0392: 
 0393:     Parameters
 0394:     ----------
 0395:     b: float
 0396:         Parameter b in the above equation.
 0397:     c: float
 0398:         Paramter c in the above equation.
 0399:     populations: np.array(n_loc, M)
 0400:         The population of each age group (total number of age group = M)
 0401:         in each location (total number of location = n_loc ).
 0402:     areas: np.array(n_loc)
 0403:         The area of each geographical region.
 0404:     coordinates: np.array(n_loc, 2)
 0405:         The GPS coordinates of each geographical region.
 0406:     '''
 0407: 
 0408:     cdef:
 0409:         Py_ssize_t n_loc, M
